  "text": "In terms of FIGO stage, although no significant difference was observed, we did find a trend for increased PFS in the IP/IV arm for patients with stage IV disease ( Supplementary Fig. S2 ). Recently, Jamieson et al. [CITATION_1] reported that the most common site of first and subsequent recurrence in stage IV disease was the abdomen, with only a small number of recurrences arising at extra-abdominal sites. Thus, we posit that ovarian cancer patients with stage IV disease may benefit from IP chemotherapy by decreasing recurrent disease in the abdomen.",
